{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give State Pension to all at 60 and increase it to equal 48hrs of Living Wage",
        "additional_details": "Hence from April 2025 a Universal State Pension should be \u00a3586.08 per week or about \u00a330,476.16 per year as a right to all including expatriates, age 60 and above.\r\n \r\nWe think that Government policy seems intent on the State Pension being a benefit not paid to all, while ever increasing the age of entitlement. We want reforms to the State Pension, so that it is available to all including expatriates, from age 60, and linked to the National Living Wage, for security.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to make the State Pension available from the age of 60 & increase this to equal 48hrs a week at the National Living Wage. ",
